# data-flow-protocols

## Crisis Conversation Flow (Importance: 90)
- Initial conversation analysis through pattern-based crisis detection
- Multi-level urgency classification triggers different routing paths:
  - Low/Medium: Automated AI responses with resource matching
  - High: Automated-to-human handoff protocols
  - Urgent: Immediate emergency response activation (988/911)

## Handoff Protocols (Importance: 85)
`src/components/EnhancedPublicChat.tsx`:
- Automated detection of escalation requirements
- Seamless transition from AI to human responders
- Status tracking through handoff states
- Real-time safety protocol integration

## Queue Management Flow (Importance: 80)
`src/components/EnhancedAdminDashboard.tsx`:
- Priority-based conversation sorting and distribution
- Active status tracking (active/needs_handoff/escalated)
- Real-time resource availability updates
- Crisis queue analytics and monitoring

## Resource Context Flow (Importance: 75)
`supabase/functions/chat/index.ts`:
- Crisis-aware routing based on resource availability
- Geographic resource mapping integration
- Service capacity monitoring
- Eligibility criteria validation
- Real-time intervention trigger processing

## Crisis Assessment Pipeline (Importance: 85)
`src/lib/aiResponses.ts`:
- Multi-stage crisis evaluation flow
- Topic categorization for resource matching
- Safety flag detection and routing
- Automated response selection based on crisis patterns
- Continuous conversation analysis for escalation triggers

